Program: Free Thinking
Title: Autobiographical Memory and Contemporary Fiction
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03g2yhx
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 5 Nov 2013
Blogs, YouTube, Facebook and phone apps have changed the way we share our lives, leading to an explosion in the telling of life stories. Alice Hall, from the University of York, explores our changing perceptions of what memory and memoir mean and looks at the way the language of modern fiction has tried to reflect this shift. Producer: Luke Mulhall. Show less